<task id="MCI-022" project="M365 Copilot Integration R1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Email Drafting via Agent</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <phase>3</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, communications, agent-gateway</tags>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>MCI-010, MCI-019</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Implement the email drafting flow for the M365 Copilot agent. When a user asks the agent
    to draft an email related to a matter or document, the service resolves the matter context,
    queries relevant activity history, calls Azure OpenAI to generate a contextual email draft,
    and returns the result as an email preview Adaptive Card with edit/send/cancel actions.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET developer experienced with Azure OpenAI integration, communications modules, and BFF API patterns</role>

  <goal>
    Deliver an EmailDraftService that generates contextual email drafts via Azure OpenAI and
    returns them as editable email preview Adaptive Cards, wrapping the existing communications
    module capabilities.
  </goal>

  <constraints>
    - Wrap existing communications module — do not reimplement email sending or activity queries
    - Use Azure OpenAI for draft generation (follow existing AI integration patterns)
    - Follow ADR-013: extend BFF, not a separate service
    - Follow AI cost and rate limit constraints from ADR-016
    - Return email-preview Adaptive Card with editable subject and body fields
    - Include Action.Submit for Edit, Send, and Cancel operations
    - Handle missing context gracefully (no matter found, no activity history)
    - Sanitize any PII from AI-generated content before including in card
    - Follow ADR-010 DI minimalism for service registration
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>docs/architecture/ai-implementation-reference.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/ai.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-010-di-minimalism.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-m365-copilot-integration/design.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-m365-copilot-integration/spec.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Review existing communications module interfaces for activity queries and email operations</step>
    <step order="2">Review ai-implementation-reference.md for Azure OpenAI integration patterns and prompt construction</step>
    <step order="3">Create EmailDraftService.cs with constructor injecting communications module, Azure OpenAI client, and AdaptiveCardFormatterService</step>
    <step order="4">Implement DraftEmailAsync method: accept matter reference, recipient hint, and user instructions</step>
    <step order="5">Implement matter resolution — look up matter and retrieve relevant activity history for context</step>
    <step order="6">Implement Azure OpenAI draft generation — construct prompt with matter context, activity summary, and user instructions; call completion API</step>
    <step order="7">Implement response formatting — pass generated draft to AdaptiveCardFormatterService to create email-preview card</step>
    <step order="8">Implement action handling — define Submit action payloads for Edit (re-draft with feedback), Send (trigger email send), and Cancel</step>
    <step order="9">Implement error handling — missing matter returns error card, AI generation failure returns error card with suggestion</step>
    <step order="10">Register service in DI and wire into Agent Gateway endpoints</step>
    <step order="11">Add unit tests for draft generation flow, error scenarios, and action payload structure</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>Read</tool>
    <tool>Write</tool>
    <tool>Edit</tool>
    <tool>Glob</tool>
    <tool>Grep</tool>
    <tool>Bash</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Features/Agent/EmailDraftService.cs</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    - EmailDraftService is registered in DI and callable from Agent Gateway endpoints
    - DraftEmailAsync accepts matter reference, recipient hint, and user instructions
    - Service resolves matter context and queries activity history from existing communications module
    - Azure OpenAI generates contextual email draft based on matter context and user instructions
    - Response is an email-preview Adaptive Card with editable subject and body
    - Edit action re-drafts with user feedback; Send action triggers email; Cancel dismisses
    - Missing matter returns descriptive error card
    - AI generation failure returns error card with retry suggestion
    - Service follows existing AI integration patterns (no custom OpenAI client setup)
    - Unit tests cover successful draft, missing matter, and AI failure scenarios
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
